&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;About xAI&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;xAI’s mission is to create AI systems that can accurately understand the universe and aid humanity in its pursuit of knowledge. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Our team is small, highly motivated, and focused on engineering excellence. This organization is for individuals who appreciate challenging themselves and thrive on curiosity. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;We operate with a flat organizational structure. All employees are expected to be hands-on and to contribute directly to the company’s mission. Leadership is given to those who show initiative and consistently deliver excellence. Work ethic and strong prioritization skills are important. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;All engineers are expected to have strong communication skills. They should be able to concisely and accurately share knowledge with their teammates.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Safety Team at X works to safeguard the user’s voice while balancing on- and off-platform safety risks through policy enforcement that promotes trust in X. As a member of the Law Enforcement Response Team within X Safety, you will focus on managing global information requests, ensuring efficient and accurate processing while supporting the team’s mission to protect user privacy and freedom of expression. This role requires a detail-oriented, collaborative, and adaptable individual who thrives in a dynamic environment and is passionate about delivering high-quality work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle global information requests, including document intake, processing, and tracking, with a focus on accuracy and timeliness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Law Enforcement Response Team members in the U.S., EMEA, and Singapore to prioritize requests and ensure consistency in operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously improve processes to enhance efficiency and consistency in handling legal requests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in an on-call rotation, working closely with the Safety Team to provide timely responses to emergency requests from around the world.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify anomalies or unusual patterns in requests and escalate ambiguous policy issues as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain open, thorough, and regular communication with teammates and cross-functional teams to support team efficiency and deliverables.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver consistent, high-quality work on repetitive tasks while managing multiple priorities in a dynamic environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take ownership of projects, seeing them through from start to finish with a focus on detail and organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in written and spoken English.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional communication and writing skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working proficiency in Japanese is required, as the role involves reviewing legal documents in that language.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with user information requests, legal documents, or a legal education.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and organizational skills, with the ability to prioritize tasks in a dynamic work environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to handle repetitive tasks while maintaining high-quality output.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion and enthusiasm for protecting user privacy and freedom of expression.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative mindset with perseverance, determination, and a proactive approach to problem-solving.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable navigating ambiguous policy escalations and making sound decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Availability to work weekends, with potential schedules including Tuesday–Saturday or Sunday–Thursday.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1+ years of experience in a Safety or Legal Operations role at a tech company, or as a paralegal, litigation support, or equivalent role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree or equivalent education/experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to spot anomalies or unusual patterns in data or requests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong sense of ownership, optimism, and enthusiasm for tackling complex challenges in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;xAI is an equal opportunity employer.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
