&lt;p&gt;As an Exceptional Engineer at xAI, you’ll own the delivery of polished, end-to-end features that delight users and scale our services. Working hand-in-hand with product and research teams, you’ll help turn cutting-edge interactions into reality, directly fueling breakthroughs that redefine what’s possible using advanced AI.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An ideal candidate meets at least the following requirements:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert knowledge of TypeScript, Python or Rust.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in designing, developing, and maintaining scalable architectures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in setting up observability best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of computer science fundamentals and type systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with Kubernetes and containerized applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in tuning production services for performance, reliability, and scalability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additionally, any of the below points will help a candidate stand out:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Founding or early engineer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Built projects end to end.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building libraries or frameworks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with microservices architecture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity functional programming principles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience gathering and analyzing user feedback.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Locations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We hire engineers in Palo Alto, and San Francisco. Our team usually works from the office 5 days a week but allow work-from-home days when required. Candidates who join in San Francisco must make it to Palo Alto at least twice a week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Process&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After submitting your application, the team reviews your CV and statement of exceptional work. If your application passes this stage, you will be invited to a 15 minute interview (“phone interview”) during which a member of our team will ask some basic questions. If you clear the initial phone interview, you will enter the main process, which consists of 2 technical interviews and 1 project deep-dive interview:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Practical coding assessment in a language of your choice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Systems design hands-on: Demonstrate practical skills in a live problem-solving session.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Project deep-dive: Present and answer questions about exceptional work that you’ve done.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Meet and greet with the wider team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our goal is to finish the main process within one week. Final interviews will be conducted in person.&lt;/p&gt;
