&lt;p&gt;You may work across the entire xAI tech stack ranging from model development to production infrastructure. This position is based in London, UK, and we will match you to a specific team at the offer stage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Not every candidate fits neatly into our typical job postings. For instance, you might have built embedded systems for spacecraft rather than large-scale distributed infrastructure—but we’ve seen time and again that engineers who excel deeply in one hard domain tend to excel in others.&lt;br&gt;At xAI, our core work is training frontier AI models and shipping products built on them. Even if you have zero background in machine learning or consumer/infrastructure software, we strongly encourage you to apply if you’re confident you can have outsized impact here. Your previous industry or tech stack is irrelevant; what matters is a clear, demonstrated history of exceptional achievement—whether that’s debugging a mission-critical issue under impossible deadlines, turning around a failing project or company, or accomplishing something widely considered unfeasible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The “statement of exceptional work” section below is the most important part of your application. Please invest extra effort: be concise, specific, and concrete.&lt;/p&gt;
