&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;xAI’s mission is to create AI systems that can accurately understand the universe and aid humanity in its pursuit of knowledge. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Our team is small, highly motivated, and focused on engineering excellence. This organization is for individuals who appreciate challenging themselves and thrive on curiosity. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;We operate with a flat organizational structure. All employees are expected to be hands-on and to contribute directly to the company’s mission. Leadership is given to those who show initiative and consistently deliver excellence. Work ethic and strong prioritization skills are important. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;All engineers are expected to have strong communication skills. They should be able to concisely and accurately share knowledge with their teammates.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 data-pm-slice=&quot;1 3 []&quot;&gt;About the Role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Facilities Maintenance Assistant at xAI Memphis, you will support the upkeep of our supercomputing data center facilities by assisting with routine non-critical maintenance tasks. Under close supervision, you&#39;ll help with basic operations and limited maintenance on critical equipment, contributing to a reliable and efficient environment that powers our AI-driven mission. This entry-level role emphasizes hands-on learning, teamwork, and attention to detail in a fast-paced setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;tight&quot; data-tight=&quot;true&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assist in performing non-critical maintenance and repair work, such as:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;tight&quot; data-tight=&quot;true&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;People door repairs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Administrative area upkeep&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Building envelope maintenance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Landscaping&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Under direct supervision of an operator, assist as required in the operation of critical equipment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assist in the performance of limited maintenance on offline critical equipment as directed, including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;tight&quot; data-tight=&quot;true&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Single chiller maintenance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Single CDU filter changeouts&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Leak detection verification in alarming racks&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support daily inspections of facilities areas to identify and report potential issues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Help maintain spare parts inventory and assist with basic organization of tools and equipment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Follow standard operating procedures (SOPs) and safety protocols during all tasks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Collaborate with team members to ensure timely completion of maintenance activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provide support during scheduled system maintenance or minor repairs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assist in documenting work performed and any observed issues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Participate in team training sessions and contribute to a collaborative work environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Basic Qualifications&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;tight&quot; data-tight=&quot;true&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;High school diploma or equivalent (relevant experience or technical certification preferred).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1+ years of experience in maintenance, facilities, or a related hands-on role (data center experience is a plus).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Basic knowledge of mechanical, electrical, or plumbing systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Familiarity with hand tools and power tools.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong attention to detail and ability to follow instructions closely.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good communication skills and a team-oriented mindset.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to prioritize tasks in a dynamic environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Preferred Skills and Experience&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;tight&quot; data-tight=&quot;true&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience in a data center or industrial facility setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Basic understanding of HVAC or electrical systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;OSHA safety certification or equivalent.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
