&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;We are seeking a highly skilled Software Engineering Specialist to join xAI’s Human Data team, where you will play a critical role in creating cutting-edge datasets to train, benchmark, and advance large language models. In this role, you will collaborate with technical staff to curate high-quality code examples, refine AI-generated code, and enhance enterprise-level AI-driven coding solutions. By leveraging your expertise in front-end development and data annotation across text, voice, and video formats, you will help teach AI models about human interactions, reactions, and problem-solving approaches. Ideal candidates are adaptable, detail-oriented, and passionate about driving innovation in a fast-paced environment to support xAI’s mission of building a trusted global digital public square.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AI model training initiatives by curating code examples, offering precise solutions, and meticulous corrections in Python, JavaScript (including ReactJS), C/C++, Java,&amp;nbsp; Rust and Go. The Front-End Specialist will focus on any and all Enterprise aspects, as listed in ‘Required Qualifications’ section.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate and refine AI-generated code, ensuring it adheres to industry standards for efficiency, scalability, and reliability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams to enhance AI-driven coding solutions, ensuring they meet enterprise-level quality and performance benchmarks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of professional front-end development experience building responsive, user-facing web applications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep expertise in &lt;strong&gt;React&lt;/strong&gt; (including hooks, context, modern state management such as Redux/Zustand/Recoil, and component lifecycle) — &lt;strong&gt;required&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong proficiency in &lt;strong&gt;Vue&lt;/strong&gt; and/or &lt;strong&gt;Angular&lt;/strong&gt; — &lt;strong&gt;big pluses&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in JavaScript (ES6+) and TypeScript&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise in CSS, Tailwind CSS, responsive design, UI interactions, and animations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid understanding of performance optimization (lazy loading, code splitting, caching strategies, asset optimization)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience implementing accessibility standards (WCAG 2.1+, ARIA roles, semantic HTML, keyboard navigation)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with SEO best practices for single-page applications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong debugging and profiling skills using browser DevTools and performance monitoring tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with testing frameworks (Jest, Vitest, React Testing Library, Playwright, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid understanding of client-server communication via REST and/or GraphQL APIs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ideal candidate for this role is adaptable, possesses strong logical reasoning skills, is detail-oriented, and thrives in a fast-paced work environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience integrating analytics, monitoring and front-end security best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with containerization technologies (Docker).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of backend technologies (python, Node.js, APIs, databases, authentication, etc.) to enable effective full-stack collaboration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Location &amp;amp; Other Expectations&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;US-based candidates cannot be hired in Wyoming or Illinois at this time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Visa sponsorship is not available.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For remote positions, candidates should have a reliable high-speed internet connection, along with a functioning camera and microphone for seamless participation in virtual meetings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
