&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;About xAI&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;xAI’s mission is to create AI systems that can accurately understand the universe and aid humanity in its pursuit of knowledge. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Our team is small, highly motivated, and focused on engineering excellence. This organization is for individuals who appreciate challenging themselves and thrive on curiosity. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;We operate with a flat organizational structure. All employees are expected to be hands-on and to contribute directly to the company’s mission. Leadership is given to those who show initiative and consistently deliver excellence. Work ethic and strong prioritization skills are important. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;All engineers are expected to have strong communication skills. They should be able to concisely and accurately share knowledge with their teammates.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;About the Role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;We are seeking a results-driven Technical Recruiter to join xAI’s Talent Acquisition team, where you will spearhead high-volume sourcing efforts to attract top-tier technical talent and fuel our mission to build the trusted global digital public square. In this role, you will own the end-to-end recruitment process for priority technical requisitions, leveraging a world-class, data-driven approach to deliver exceptional candidate experiences and meet aggressive hiring goals. Ideal candidates are go-getters who thrive in fast-paced, startup-like environments, excel at building creative sourcing strategies, and are passionate about scaling xAI’s workforce with top talent across all technical disciplines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with technical leaders to deeply understand requirements for priority hires and develop high-volume sourcing strategies to match top talent to open roles at speed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage a robust, full-cycle hiring process, including sourcing, screening, and closing candidates for both high-volume and niche technical roles across all available channels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage data to optimize candidate ROI, increase conversion rates, streamline processes, keep stakeholders informed of hiring trends, and monitor recruitment pace to meet ambitious targets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create frameworks to analyze the talent market and align sourcing strategies with xAI’s needs for technical roles, including research positions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure an exceptional candidate experience at every stage of the recruitment journey, from initial outreach to offer acceptance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of recruiting experience in fast-paced, hyper-growth environments, either in agency or in-house settings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of managing high-volume pipelines and specialty technical positions, delivering measurable results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outcome-oriented with strong analytical skills and a demonstrated ability to make data-driven decisions in ambiguous environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full-cycle recruiting experience, including expertise in challenging closes, stakeholder management, and building key internal partnerships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and collaboration skills to work effectively with technical leaders and cross-functional teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using Greenhouse ATS to manage high-volume recruitment workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven success supporting hiring events and analyzing post-event ROI to drive recruitment strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with talent attraction techniques and staying current with market trends to inform sourcing strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience recruiting at a high-growth startup, building scalable talent acquisition solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise in hiring candidates across all technical disciplines, including research roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proactive, adaptable mindset with a touch of humor to thrive in a dynamic, mission-driven environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location, Hourly, and Other Expectations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This position is based in Palo Alto, CA, or fully remote.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Palo Alto option is an in-office role requiring 5 days per week; remote positions require strong self-motivation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For those who will be working from a personal device, please note your computer must be a Chromebook, Mac with MacOS 11.0 or later, or Windows 10 or later.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You must own and have reliable access to a smartphone.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Annual Salary Range&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;$40,000 - $120,000 USD&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Benefits&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Base salary is just one part of our total rewards package at xAI, which also includes equity, comprehensive medical, vision, and dental coverage, access to a 401(k) retirement plan, short &amp;amp; long-term disability insurance, life insurance, and various other discounts and perks.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;xAI is an equal opportunity employer.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
