&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;About xAI&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;xAI’s mission is to create AI systems that can accurately understand the universe and aid humanity in its pursuit of knowledge. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Our team is small, highly motivated, and focused on engineering excellence. This organization is for individuals who appreciate challenging themselves and thrive on curiosity. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;We operate with a flat organizational structure. All employees are expected to be hands-on and to contribute directly to the company’s mission. Leadership is given to those who show initiative and consistently deliver excellence. Work ethic and strong prioritization skills are important. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;All engineers are expected to have strong communication skills. They should be able to concisely and accurately share knowledge with their teammates.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Data Center Fabrics are the foundational building blocks of the complex architecture that enables Grok to be trained and serve customer queries as they learn to understand the universe. To enable us to move faster we are looking for a Core Network Engineering Team Lead in our Palo Alto Office. You will develop and execute the team’s roadmap in collaboration with partner teams. You will guide your team and directly contribute to its network&#39;s development, while hiring and developing the world class talent xAI needs to achieve AGI.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute the team’s roadmap for data center network fabrics in collaboration with partner teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and mentor a team of engineers, providing technical guidance and feedback to ensure high performance and growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Directly contribute to the design, development, and optimization of network infrastructure to maximize availability and performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write Python scripts to automate processes, optimize compute resources, and reduce repetitive engineering tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with cross-functional teams to align on roadmaps and resolve break/fix issues efficiently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hire and develop top-tier talent to support xAI’s mission of achieving AGI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ruthlessly prioritize team efforts to maximize weekly impact for customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years as a technical lead in AI networking, with at least 8 years of experience in hyperscale network environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Python scripting to optimize compute resources and automate engineering tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience with RoCEv2 and/or InfiniBand technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to deliver highly available and performant data center network fabrics through individual and team contributions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience mentoring engineers and providing constructive feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to navigate ambiguity and drive progress without being hindered by over-analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong collaboration skills to align multiple teams on cohesive roadmaps and solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proactive, hands-on approach to tackling challenges, with no task considered too small.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in high-stakes environments requiring rapid prioritization and decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with recruiting and developing world-class engineering talent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Annual Base Salary&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;$180,000 - $440,000 USD&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Base salary is just one part of our total rewards package at X, which also includes equity, comprehensive medical, vision, and dental coverage, access to a 401(k) retirement plan, short &amp;amp; long-term disability insurance, life insurance, and various other discounts and perks.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;xAI is an equal opportunity employer.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://data.x.ai/ccpa_personnel_privacy_notice.pdf&quot;&gt;California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) Notice&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;About xAI&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;xAI’s mission is to create AI systems that can accurately understand the universe and aid humanity in its pursuit of knowledge. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Our team is small, highly motivated, and focused on engineering excellence. This organization is for individuals who appreciate challenging themselves and thrive on curiosity. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;We operate with a flat organizational structure. All employees are expected to be hands-on and to contribute directly to the company’s mission. Leadership is given to those who show initiative and consistently deliver excellence. Work ethic and strong prioritization skills are important. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;All engineers are expected to have strong communication skills. They should be able to concisely and accurately share knowledge with their teammates.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;About the Role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a dedicated and strategic Manager, HR Operations to join xAI’s People Operations team, where you will lead a global team in delivering seamless HR support to employees and stakeholders across offices worldwide. In this role, you will oversee the entire employee lifecycle, drive process improvements, and ensure data integrity and compliance, all while fostering a positive employee experience. Ideal candidates are consummate professionals with a passion for confidentiality, operational excellence, and scalability, thriving in a fast-paced, dynamic environment to support xAI’s mission of building a trusted global digital public square.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;p-rich_text_list p-rich_text_list__bullet p-rich_text_list--nested&quot; data-stringify-type=&quot;unordered-list&quot; data-list-tree=&quot;true&quot; data-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Lead, train, and support a global HR team of professionals across the US, UK, and Singapore.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Oversee the whole employee life cycle processes across the globe, guaranteeing consistency and efficiency across all regions including: sending offer letters, managing onboarding (eg., conducting I9s, background checks, access requests), conducting new hire orientation, processing employee data changes (eg, promotions, transfers, compensation adjustments), answering employee and former employee HR questions, managing all offboarding.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Design and execute HR Ops policies including those in our employee handbook (eg., PTO accrual, overtime allocations and hourly schedules, global leaves of absences, one time payments and clawbacks)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Responsibility for contractor, consultant, and vendor management globally (partnering with Finance on expense, onboarding, offboarding, contract renews / extensions).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Enable scalability through process improvements and automation. Constantly finding ways to make our operations and processes better and faster.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Create, maintain and audit employee files ensuring data integrity and compliance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree or equivalent experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of HR generalist experience, with a strong preference for the technology industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience as a People Manager, leading HR teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In-depth knowledge of global HR regulatory requirements and labor laws.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Workday and Jira or other ticketing systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong Excel skills for data analysis and reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional organizational skills, with the ability to prioritize tasks, maintain confidentiality, and complete work with accuracy and efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent interpersonal skills, with a client-service mindset and the ability to build strong partnerships with HR, Recruiting, IT, Finance, Legal, Mobility, and People Systems &amp;amp; Analytics teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience driving HR operations in a fast-paced, high-growth tech startup environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to lead global HR projects and implement scalable process improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with automation tools or technologies to enhance HR operational efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proactive mindset, with a passion for identifying and recommending continuous process improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong collaboration skills, with experience partnering across diverse, global teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A sense of adaptability and a touch of humor to thrive in a dynamic, mission-driven organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Annual Salary Range&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;$142,000 - $259,000 USD&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Benefits&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Base salary is just one part of our total rewards package at xAI, which also includes equity, comprehensive medical, vision, and dental coverage, access to a 401(k) retirement plan, short &amp;amp; long-term disability insurance, life insurance, and various other discounts and perks.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;xAI is an equal opportunity employer.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://data.x.ai/ccpa_personnel_privacy_notice.pdf&quot;&gt;California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) Notice&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;About xAI&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;xAI’s mission is to create AI systems that can accurately understand the universe and aid humanity in its pursuit of knowledge. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Our team is small, highly motivated, and focused on engineering excellence. This organization is for individuals who appreciate challenging themselves and thrive on curiosity. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;We operate with a flat organizational structure. All employees are expected to be hands-on and to contribute directly to the company’s mission. Leadership is given to those who show initiative and consistently deliver excellence. Work ethic and strong prioritization skills are important. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;All engineers are expected to have strong communication skills. They should be able to concisely and accurately share knowledge with their teammates.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an AI Tutor - Materials Science Specialist at xAI, you will be instrumental in enhancing our cutting-edge AI technologies by providing high-quality input and labels using specialized software. You will collaborate closely with our technical team to support the training of new AI tasks, contributing to innovative initiatives. Your responsibilities include refining annotation tools and selecting complex problems from advanced materials science fields to drive significant improvements in model performance. This involves gathering or providing data in text, voice, and video formats, including annotations, audio recordings, or video sessions—tasks with which you must be comfortable and eager to engage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position demands a dynamic approach to learning and adapting in a fast-paced environment, where your ability to interpret and execute tasks based on evolving instructions is crucial.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The AI Tutor - Materials Science Specialist role is a remote position. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;We prefer candidates available for full-time employment, but exceptional applicants seeking part-time opportunities will also be considered&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt; (please see the bottom of this job description for more details).&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use proprietary software applications to provide input/labels on defined projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support and ensure the delivery of high-quality curated data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Play a pivotal role in supporting and contributing to the training of new tasks, working closely with the technical staff to ensure the successful development and implementation of cutting-edge initiatives/technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interact with the technical staff to help improve the design of efficient annotation tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solve problems that help drive innovation in materials by guiding AI models to enhance research in specialized areas, improving outcomes in scientific discovery and application.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Choose problems from various fields across materials science that align with your specialization, where you can confidently provide detailed solutions and evaluate model responses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regularly interpret, analyze, and execute tasks based on given instructions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Master’s or PhD in materials science, physics, chemistry, chemical engineering, or a highly related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise and specialization in a materials-related subdomain, including but not limited to energy materials, semiconductors, nanomaterials, metals, alloys, biomaterials, polymers, elastomers, ceramics, or glasses.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in reading and writing, both in informal and professional English.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong ability to navigate various information resources, databases, and online resources is essential.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outstanding communication, interpersonal, analytical, and organizational capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid reading comprehension skills combined with the capacity to exercise autonomous judgment even when presented with limited data/material.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong passion for and commitment to technological advancements and innovation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced expertise in materials science, demonstrated by multiple publications, or patents, preferably with one or more first-author papers, in reputable peer-reviewed journals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous AI Tutoring experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Teaching experience (as a professor, teacher, or tutor).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in technical writing, journalism, or a professional writing setting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location, Hourly, and Other Expectations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This position is based in Palo Alto, CA, or fully remote.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Palo Alto option is an in-office role requiring 5 days per week; remote positions require strong self-motivation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If you are based in the US, please note we are unable to hire in the states of Wyoming and Illinois at this time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We are unable to provide visa sponsorship.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team members are expected to work from 9:00am - 5:30pm PST for the first two weeks of training and 9:00am - 5:30pm in their own timezone thereafter.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For those who will be working from a personal device, please note your computer must be a Chromebook, Mac with MacOS 11.0 or later, or Windows 10 or later.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You must own and have reliable access to a smartphone.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Compensation&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;$45/hour - $75/hour&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The posted pay range is intended for U.S.-based candidates and depends on factors including relevant experience, skills, education, geographic location, and qualifications. For international candidates, our recruiting team can provide an estimated pay range for your location.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hourly pay is just one part of our total rewards package at xAI. Specific benefits vary by country, depending on your country of residence you may have access to medical benefits. We do not offer benefits for part-time roles.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;xAI is an equal opportunity employer.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://data.x.ai/ccpa_personnel_privacy_notice.pdf&quot;&gt;California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) Notice&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;About xAI&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;xAI’s mission is to create AI systems that can accurately understand the universe and aid humanity in its pursuit of knowledge. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Our team is small, highly motivated, and focused on engineering excellence. This organization is for individuals who appreciate challenging themselves and thrive on curiosity. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;We operate with a flat organizational structure. All employees are expected to be hands-on and to contribute directly to the company’s mission. Leadership is given to those who show initiative and consistently deliver excellence. Work ethic and strong prioritization skills are important. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;All engineers are expected to have strong communication skills. They should be able to concisely and accurately share knowledge with their teammates.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Mechanical Design Engineer on our AI Hardware team, you will design and develop mechanical systems for cutting-edge AI hardware at our Memphis datacenters. Your expertise in CAD, mechanical design, and end-user products will drive the creation of reliable, high-performance solutions that power xAI’s mission-critical systems.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design mechanical components, including enclosures, cooling systems, and structural assemblies, using CAD tools (e.g., SolidWorks, Autodesk Fusion).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and test prototypes, performing stress, thermal, and performance analyses to ensure designs meet end-user and datacenter requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including electrical engineers and product managers, to integrate mechanical designs into AI hardware systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize designs for manufacturability, cost, and performance in high-density computing environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create detailed technical drawings, specifications, and documentation for manufacturing and assembly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Innovate to develop mechanical solutions that enhance the efficiency and reliability of AI hardware.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years in mechanical design, with a focus on end-user products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in CAD software (e.g., SolidWorks, AutoCAD, CATIA).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with high-performance computing hardware, datacenter systems, or consumer electronics is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with AI hardware requirements, such as advanced cooling systems or ruggedized designs for datacenter applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise in mechanical design principles, including material selection, thermal management, and structural analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with prototyping, testing, and iterative design processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of manufacturing techniques (e.g., CNC machining, injection molding, sheet metal fabrication).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong problem-solving skills and meticulous attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to thrive in a collaborative, fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;xAI is an equal opportunity employer.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://data.x.ai/ccpa_personnel_privacy_notice.pdf&quot;&gt;California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) Notice&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

