&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;About xAI&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;xAI’s mission is to create AI systems that can accurately understand the universe and aid humanity in its pursuit of knowledge. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Our team is small, highly motivated, and focused on engineering excellence. This organization is for individuals who appreciate challenging themselves and thrive on curiosity. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;We operate with a flat organizational structure. All employees are expected to be hands-on and to contribute directly to the company’s mission. Leadership is given to those who show initiative and consistently deliver excellence. Work ethic and strong prioritization skills are important. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;All engineers are expected to have strong communication skills. They should be able to concisely and accurately share knowledge with their teammates.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;xAI is building at a furious pace with the latest hardware to help people understand the universe. We are in need of a Network Deployment Engineer that has spent the last 8 years automating away human cycles required to build and maintain hyper scale production networks that reside in data centers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will own xAI’s network deployment speed and accuracy, creating automation, workflows and&amp;nbsp; dashboards leveraging our modelling, source of truth and provisioning software systems. Your tools will be used by the team and technicians to build tens of thousands of devices and millions of links for our different data center and backbone topologies. Then, your tooling will keep the network perpetually consistent for configuration and operating system versions, from simple deploy and forget to complex sequencing for topology changes. You will help us remove tens of thousands of repetitive human cycles a year and keep our team small and nimble.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Responsibilities Will Include&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaise with engineers from different teams to build strategies and roadmaps that will address short term needs while ensuring a long term vision is met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use python to create an ecosystem of tools and dashboards that onsite technicians can use to build our network products and maintain it with minimal human cycles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of experience in using python to automate hyper scale networks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years in the networking industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years in a team lead role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of networking topologies, protocols and best practices (e.g., BGP, OSPF, ROCEv2 etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Preferred Experiences&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in AI/ML infrastructure or large-scale GPU clusters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong problem-solving skills and ability to thrive in a fast-paced, ambiguous setting.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work will be in-office based out of either Palo Alto, California, Dublin, Ireland or Seattle, Washington. There will be significant travel expected to data center buildouts. For Dublin and Seattle based employees, additional travel to our head office in Palo Alto will be required for team collaboration. Travel to Memphis may account for up to 25-30% of time during peak buildout phases.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;xAI is an equal opportunity employer.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://data.x.ai/ccpa_personnel_privacy_notice.pdf&quot;&gt;California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) Notice&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;About xAI&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;xAI’s mission is to create AI systems that can accurately understand the universe and aid humanity in its pursuit of knowledge. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Our team is small, highly motivated, and focused on engineering excellence. This organization is for individuals who appreciate challenging themselves and thrive on curiosity. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;We operate with a flat organizational structure. All employees are expected to be hands-on and to contribute directly to the company’s mission. Leadership is given to those who show initiative and consistently deliver excellence. Work ethic and strong prioritization skills are important. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;All engineers are expected to have strong communication skills. They should be able to concisely and accurately share knowledge with their teammates.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;xAI is building at a furious pace with the latest hardware to help people understand the universe and we are in need of Network Development Engineers (NDEs) with at least 3+ years of experience in deploying or operating large scale production Data Center or Backbone networks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will own the availability and/or the deployment of production networks for 𝕏 and xAI, including Data Center, Backbone networks and our primary front and backend networks that train Grok and our customers use for inference. Deployment Engineers will own all aspects of planning and building of green and brownfield network deployments. Operations Engineers will own timely mitigation of network impairments for all layers of our network and the return to service of Network HW and capacity You will be expected to participate in a team oncall rota and to contribute to scaling and maintenance efforts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deploying or Operating scalable network architectures for AI/HPC workloads, inter-DC and Backbone network fabrics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Power user and ability to iterate SW and toolings for network operations, network deployment and monitoring.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating with cross-functional teams on data center &amp;amp; backbone buildouts and optimizations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyzing performance and availability metrics to identify and resolve bottlenecks, availability impairments or inefficient build processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring high availability, fast deployability and high security of production networks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A minimum of 3 years in deploying or operating hyper scale networks&lt;/li&gt;
