&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;About xAI&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;xAI’s mission is to create AI systems that can accurately understand the universe and aid humanity in its pursuit of knowledge. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Our team is small, highly motivated, and focused on engineering excellence. This organization is for individuals who appreciate challenging themselves and thrive on curiosity. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;We operate with a flat organizational structure. All employees are expected to be hands-on and to contribute directly to the company’s mission. Leadership is given to those who show initiative and consistently deliver excellence. Work ethic and strong prioritization skills are important. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;All engineers are expected to have strong communication skills. They should be able to concisely and accurately share knowledge with their teammates.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re seeking a Senior Leader to join our Corporate Security Team leading operations in APAC. You’ll design, implement, and manage physical security systems to protect our people and facilities in a high-threat environment. Working with global teams, you’ll deliver cost-effective, innovative solutions while upholding the highest standards of security and operational excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead security operations team in APAC to include complex access issues, event coverage and incident response (e.g. respond to trespassers, protests, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with relevant business partners in APAC to deliver security services in a manner that enhances the business and ensures business continuity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage, train and support current CorpSec team in APAC and its staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with protection strategies for xAI Team members in APAC with higher risk profiles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaise with relevant law enforcement to proactively identify risks and respond to security incidents that require law enforcement support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage CorpSec travel security program for APAC including travel to high risk areas&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead physical security crisis management efforts for APAC&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Think critically about our physical security risks to our employees&#39; and facilities and design and implement and manage security that mitigate those risks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with xAI&#39;s Corporate Security team to find, implement and maintain technology based solutions to our very dynamic set of&amp;nbsp; physical security challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing SOPs and other documentation for system architecture and security system standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assisting with physical security audits&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with xAI Team members to find confidential technology, uniformed guard or security engineering solutions to address their physical security challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentoring colleagues learn and grow through constructive and supportive feedback sessions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Looking for opportunities to grow and learn.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Note: This role may require up to 40% travel and participation in a flexible on-call rotation.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;12+ years experience in the security industry and relevant field (military / law enforcement) with related university degree / professional certificates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years experience in security operations in APAC&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to learn how to, or past experience with, analyzing and visualizing data to create useful metrics for the corporate security team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re willing to be periodically part of an out-of-hours on-call schedule&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience with Crisis Management and leadership with diverse partners.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to communicate effectively in APAC&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;xAI is an equal opportunity employer.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
