&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;About xAI&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;xAI’s mission is to create AI systems that can accurately understand the universe and aid humanity in its pursuit of knowledge. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Our team is small, highly motivated, and focused on engineering excellence. This organization is for individuals who appreciate challenging themselves and thrive on curiosity. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;We operate with a flat organizational structure. All employees are expected to be hands-on and to contribute directly to the company’s mission. Leadership is given to those who show initiative and consistently deliver excellence. Work ethic and strong prioritization skills are important. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;All engineers are expected to have strong communication skills. They should be able to concisely and accurately share knowledge with their teammates.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;About xAI&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;xAI is dedicated to accelerating human scientific discovery through artificial intelligence. Our mission is to advance our collective understanding of the universe by building AI that empowers researchers and scientists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About the Role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Strategic Project Lead on xAI’s Human Data team, you will drive the operational execution of data generation projects critical to developing advanced AI models. This hands-on role involves managing the full lifecycle of data creation, coordinating large-scale distributed teams, and ensuring high-quality deliverables under tight deadlines. You will work closely with xAI’s AI researchers to align operations with research goals, optimize processes, and maintain rigorous standards. This position is ideal for proactive leaders who thrive in fast-paced, high-stakes environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and execute end-to-end data generation workflows, translating research needs into efficient, scalable processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and resolve operational bottlenecks by implementing improvements such as optimized task sequencing, refined guidelines, incentive structures, and scalable quality controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage a distributed network of contributors, overseeing recruitment, onboarding, training, and performance to ensure consistent execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the primary point of contact for xAI’s AI research teams, delivering clear updates, anticipating needs, and fostering collaborative relationships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead daily project syncs to address challenges proactively and provide transparent progress reports to stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years in high-intensity operational roles, such as consulting, tech startups, or similar fast-paced environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical, organizational, and communication skills with a proven ability to manage complex, time-sensitive projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work in dynamic settings with tight deadlines and a focus on execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing large-scale distributed teams or workflows, ideally in data operations or AI-related projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with machine learning data pipelines or AI model development processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of implementing process improvements that enhance efficiency and quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for xAI’s mission to advance human scientific discovery through AI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proactive, resilient mindset with the ability to maintain focus and humor in high-pressure situations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Location and Expectations&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This role is based in Palo Alto, CA, with an in-office requirement of 5 days per week (Monday–Friday; occasional weekend support may be needed for critical milestones).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reliable access to a smartphone is required for coordination.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
