&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;xAI’s mission is to create AI systems that can accurately understand the universe and aid humanity in its pursuit of knowledge. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Our team is small, highly motivated, and focused on engineering excellence. This organization is for individuals who appreciate challenging themselves and thrive on curiosity. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;We operate with a flat organizational structure. All employees are expected to be hands-on and to contribute directly to the company’s mission. Leadership is given to those who show initiative and consistently deliver excellence. Work ethic and strong prioritization skills are important. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;All engineers are expected to have strong communication skills. They should be able to concisely and accurately share knowledge with their teammates.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;About the Role&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will design, deploy, and optimize large-scale battery energy storage systems (BESS) that power xAI’s AI training superclusters in Memphis. These systems, built on Tesla Megapack platforms, must deliver uninterrupted, high-density power at multi-megawatt scale while maintaining extreme reliability under variable AI workloads. You will own the end-to-end lifecycle—from site planning and integration to real-time performance tuning and long-term degradation management—ensuring the storage fleet exceeds 99.999% availability and maximizes round-trip efficiency.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead electrical, mechanical, and thermal integration of Megapack-based BESS with on-site substations, inverters, and AI compute loads.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop control strategies and firmware logic for dynamic load balancing, peak shaving, and frequency regulation tailored to AI training power profiles.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform capacity modeling, cycle-life forecasting, and degradation analysis using field telemetry and digital-twin simulations.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commission systems, validate nameplate performance, and implement predictive maintenance protocols to minimize downtime.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Tesla Energy teams on custom firmware, hardware revisions, and supply-chain scaling for xAI-specific duty cycles.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with NEC, NFPA, IEEE 1547, and local grid interconnection requirements; author interconnection studies and reliability reports.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive root-cause investigations for any energy anomalies and implement corrective actions across the fleet.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BS or MS in Electrical, Mechanical, or Energy Systems Engineering.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years in utility-scale BESS or industrial power systems.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with lithium-ion systems ≥10 MWh, including PCS, BMS, EMS, and SCADA integration.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in power system modeling tools (PSSE, PSCAD, ETAP) and control programming (Python, MATLAB, IEC 61850).&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to manage multi-disciplinary projects under aggressive timelines.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to be on-site in Memphis for commissioning and critical operations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior work with Tesla Megapack or Powerwall deployments.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PE license or NABCEP certification.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in AI/datacenter power architectures or microgrid controls.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;xAI is an equal opportunity employer.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
